## OUTPUT FORMAT REQUIREMENTS\
\
1. **Tables over prose.** Data density is more valuable than narrative.\
2. **Source every data point.** Publisher name, publication date, URL if available.\
3. **Confidence level on every row.** High = official/verified data. Medium = reputable estimate. Low = extrapolation. Estimated = calculated from other data points.\
4. **"No reliable data found"** is an acceptable answer. Do not fill gaps with speculation.\
5. **Local language terms are mandatory** for Section 2 (topics) and Section 1 (search language). We need the exact words consumers use, not translations of English concepts.\
6. **Distinguish between markets clearly.** China \uc0\u8800  Taiwan \u8800  Hong Kong \u8800  Singapore. Never aggregate "Greater China" without also breaking out individual markets.\
